1
00:00:10,067 --> 00:00:12,900
<i>You shouldn't be competing
with your brother.</i>

2
00:00:13,033 --> 00:00:15,800
<i>I have to. That's the only way
anyone ever notices me.</i>

3
00:00:15,933 --> 00:00:19,233
<i>I want to keep Mr. Valderrama
as one of our valued clients.</i>

4
00:00:19,367 --> 00:00:22,433
<i>So I want you to go see him
and apologize in person.</i>

5
00:00:22,567 --> 00:00:23,967
<i>We should celebrate this moment.</i>

6
00:00:24,100 --> 00:00:25,400
<i> Cheers.</i>

7
00:00:25,533 --> 00:00:27,400
<i>Please call Miss Castillo
to my office.</i>

8
00:00:27,533 --> 00:00:30,400
<i>Your dad sent her to meet
Mr. Valderrama.</i>

9
00:00:30,533 --> 00:00:31,900
<i> Mr. Valderrama!</i>

10
00:00:34,800 --> 00:00:37,533
<i>I'm pulling out all our
investments from your company!</i>

11
00:00:37,667 --> 00:00:38,700
<i> Don't threaten me!</i>

12
00:00:38,833 --> 00:00:40,367
<i>I could sue you
for attempted rape!</i>

13
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:42,633
<i>I saw you at the ER.
What was that about?</i>

14
00:00:42,767 --> 00:00:45,067
<i>Are you acting like this because
you have a crush on Marj?</i>

15
00:00:45,200 --> 00:00:47,367
<i>I really like her a lot.
What about you, do you like her?</i>

16
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:49,433
<i>Why won't you let me see it?
Who's that?</i>

17
00:00:49,567 --> 00:00:51,367
<i> Mom, are you texting Dad?</i>

18
00:00:52,700 --> 00:00:55,400
What is this? Are you falling
for his lies again?

19
00:00:56,733 --> 00:01:01,100
Marj, your dad
has changed.

20
00:01:01,233 --> 00:01:03,233
He promised me he would.

21
00:01:03,367 --> 00:01:05,533
You can read his messages.

22
00:01:05,667 --> 00:01:10,033
Mom, have you forgotten
what he did to you?

23
00:01:10,200 --> 00:01:16,467
The moment he finds someone
else, he'll leave you again.

24
00:01:16,600 --> 00:01:20,600
But Marj, your dad
already apologized to me.

25
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:23,533
What was I supposed to do?

26
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:26,567
Mom, come on!

27
00:01:26,700 --> 00:01:29,100
Just because he said sorry,
you're going to forgive him?

28
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:31,133
You take him back?

29
00:01:31,267 --> 00:01:33,800
If Randall apologized to me,
does that make everything okay?

30
00:01:33,933 --> 00:01:35,233
Just like that?

31
00:01:36,600 --> 00:01:38,400
Mom!

32
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:42,800
Have you forgotten what father
did to you?

33
00:01:42,967 --> 00:01:45,167
You're letting yourself
be fooled again!

34
00:01:45,300 --> 00:01:48,900
Men like that don't deserve
a second chance.

35
00:01:49,033 --> 00:01:53,867
Not a third, not a fourth,
since they'll just do it again.

36
00:01:54,000 --> 00:01:56,633
Has your heart really
turned to stone?

37
00:01:57,600 --> 00:01:59,233
I don't know.

38
00:01:59,367 --> 00:02:00,667
I don't know, Mom.

39
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:03,700
No.

40
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:05,167
I'm not into her, okay?

41
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:09,433
If you like her, go for her.

42
00:02:09,567 --> 00:02:11,300
No one's stopping you.

43
00:02:20,967 --> 00:02:24,133
I once gave my whole heart
to someone.

44
00:02:24,267 --> 00:02:27,267
Look what Randall did to me.

45
00:02:27,400 --> 00:02:29,533
We shouldn't expect anything
from men who cheat

46
00:02:29,667 --> 00:02:34,067
and take advantage like Dad.

47
00:02:34,200 --> 00:02:36,900
Because it'll only hurt more.

48
00:02:38,733 --> 00:02:40,100
Mom.

49
00:02:41,767 --> 00:02:43,900
Listen to me.

50
00:02:44,033 --> 00:02:47,400
Look at me.

51
00:02:47,567 --> 00:02:49,867
Think about Jobert and me.

52
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:52,167
Your children.

53
00:02:52,300 --> 00:02:55,000
We're here for you.

54
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,367
Please help me.

55
00:03:06,267 --> 00:03:09,233
Can you promise me something?

56
00:03:09,367 --> 00:03:12,867
Promise me
you'll never see Dad again.

57
00:04:09,167 --> 00:04:15,033
After what we lost
with Mr. Valderrama,

58
00:04:15,167 --> 00:04:20,200
we must recover by acquiring
more exclusive listings,

59
00:04:20,333 --> 00:04:22,233
specifically...

60
00:04:22,367 --> 00:04:24,900
Paradiso Escaño.

61
00:04:25,033 --> 00:04:30,333
It's a private membership
resort and residential community

62
00:04:30,500 --> 00:04:32,767
by Escaño &amp; Sons in Batangas.

63
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:33,933
But Dad,

64
00:04:34,067 --> 00:04:35,467
I thought Mr. Escaño

65
00:04:35,600 --> 00:04:39,900
was building something
in Central Visayas?

66
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:41,600
That was the original plan.

67
00:04:41,733 --> 00:04:44,700
But it seems that they're
expanding and exploring

68
00:04:44,833 --> 00:04:47,533
other locations nationwide.

69
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:50,600
Bro, why don't you team up
with Marj...

70
00:04:52,133 --> 00:04:53,867
to win over Mr. Escaño?

71
00:04:54,000 --> 00:04:56,767
She speaks Visayan, right?

72
00:04:56,900 --> 00:05:00,367
I think that will work
to your advantage.

73
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,133
No, no.

74
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:04,967
You're the one I'm sending.

75
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,367
Come on, Dad.

76
00:05:06,500 --> 00:05:08,633
Edward and Marj
are the perfect couple.

77
00:05:08,767 --> 00:05:10,433
I mean, the pair to send.

78
00:05:10,567 --> 00:05:14,533
Take a look at what they
did with the Sutherland account.

79
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:19,800
Miss Castillo is a newbie.

80
00:05:21,333 --> 00:05:22,300
In our company.

81
00:05:22,433 --> 00:05:24,067
But not in the industry.

82
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:27,200
Dad, I think it's a good idea.

83
00:05:27,333 --> 00:05:29,567
Marj speaks Cebuano.

84
00:05:29,700 --> 00:05:32,400
And she knows Batangas well
because she used to live there.

85
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:33,933
Right?

86
00:05:35,567 --> 00:05:37,533
Yes.

87
00:05:37,667 --> 00:05:38,900
Fine.

88
00:05:39,033 --> 00:05:42,933
Consider this your chance to
prove yourself, Miss Castillo.

89
00:05:43,067 --> 00:05:45,333
Bring back good news.

90
00:05:48,900 --> 00:05:50,300
Meeting adjourned.

91
00:05:52,500 --> 00:05:53,933
Thanks, Dad.

92
00:05:55,100 --> 00:05:57,800
This is your shot, bro.

93
00:05:57,933 --> 00:05:59,700
Thanks, Pao.

94
00:06:21,067 --> 00:06:23,967
Mom, I'm going to Batangas.

95
00:06:24,100 --> 00:06:26,567
I have a project
to handle there.

96
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:28,300
Batangas?

97
00:06:28,433 --> 00:06:30,567
Are you sure
you want to go back?

98
00:06:32,300 --> 00:06:34,567
That whole scandal there
is still pretty recent.

99
00:06:35,767 --> 00:06:40,000
You're reopening things you were
supposed to forget.

100
00:06:40,133 --> 00:06:42,333
I thought about saying no,
but...

101
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:45,933
why should I avoid it?

102
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:50,433
I didn't do anything wrong.

103
00:06:53,533 --> 00:06:54,867
And besides...

104
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,600
Edward's project is huge.

105
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:03,433
If it succeeds, maybe it'll
erase all the bad memories.

106
00:07:06,533 --> 00:07:12,900
Instead of running
from the past,

107
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:15,633
you should face it bravely.

108
00:07:17,033 --> 00:07:19,667
So you can
finally move on.

109
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:29,067
Mom, please watch Jobert.

110
00:07:30,433 --> 00:07:33,133
Don't let him out of your sight.

111
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:36,400
How is that any different

112
00:07:36,533 --> 00:07:40,033
from what I already do
while you're at work?

113
00:08:05,500 --> 00:08:07,267
What are you doing here, Sir?

114
00:08:08,933 --> 00:08:10,300
No more "Sir," remember?

115
00:08:10,433 --> 00:08:12,533
And no good morning?

116
00:08:12,667 --> 00:08:16,533
Or do you not want to see me?

117
00:08:16,667 --> 00:08:19,067
Oh, sorry. Good morning.

118
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:21,733
It's not that I'm unhappy.

119
00:08:21,900 --> 00:08:25,233
I was just wondering
where Edward was.

120
00:08:25,367 --> 00:08:27,633
He can't make it.
That's why I'm here.

121
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:30,333
I'll be going with
you to Batangas.

122
00:08:38,267 --> 00:08:40,667
Back to your hometown?

123
00:08:40,800 --> 00:08:42,100
Let's go.

124
00:09:05,700 --> 00:09:08,733
Didn't you say
you were going to Batangas?

125
00:09:09,967 --> 00:09:12,100
I was.

126
00:09:12,233 --> 00:09:14,433
But Dad suddenly gave me
something else to do.

127
00:09:15,767 --> 00:09:17,967
I was really looking forward
to that trip because...

128
00:09:19,800 --> 00:09:21,533
I was supposed to be with Marj.

129
00:09:23,467 --> 00:09:25,600
So...

130
00:09:25,733 --> 00:09:27,900
are you saying
you're liking this Marj?

131
00:09:31,400 --> 00:09:32,767
Let it go.

132
00:09:32,900 --> 00:09:33,967
There'll be a next time.

133
00:09:34,100 --> 00:09:37,167
You'll have plenty
of trips together.

134
00:09:41,433 --> 00:09:43,633
Edward, my son.

135
00:09:45,933 --> 00:09:47,233
It's just a shame, Mom.

136
00:09:48,633 --> 00:09:50,467
I planned the
whole weekend.

137
00:09:52,300 --> 00:09:53,567
That was supposed to be...

138
00:09:54,633 --> 00:09:59,100
That was supposed to be my
chance to impress Marj.

139
00:09:59,233 --> 00:10:03,700
You don't need to try so
hard for her to like you.

140
00:10:06,067 --> 00:10:08,167
You're a Torrecampo.

141
00:10:08,300 --> 00:10:12,300
I don't see any reason why
Marj wouldn't like you.

142
00:10:14,467 --> 00:10:15,800
No reason.

143
00:10:16,833 --> 00:10:18,167
Unless...

144
00:10:19,233 --> 00:10:21,067
Paolo becomes
my competition.

145
00:10:23,933 --> 00:10:25,600
Come on.

146
00:10:25,733 --> 00:10:27,833
Don't think like that.

147
00:10:50,867 --> 00:10:54,633
So why can't Edward go
all of a sudden?

148
00:10:54,767 --> 00:10:56,567
Dad reassigned him
to a VIP client.

149
00:10:56,700 --> 00:10:58,400
Apparently, the client
requested him personally.

150
00:11:00,133 --> 00:11:01,367
Is that so?

151
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:03,833
You already miss him?

152
00:11:06,400 --> 00:11:07,800
Can't I just be curious?

153
00:11:07,967 --> 00:11:10,467
You're putting meaning
into my question way too fast.

154
00:11:10,600 --> 00:11:11,933
Why?

155
00:11:12,067 --> 00:11:13,867
Don't you like my brother?

156
00:11:15,500 --> 00:11:19,433
I've been burned too many times
to even think about that stuff.

157
00:11:19,567 --> 00:11:21,467
Why?

158
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:23,867
Because all men cheat.

159
00:11:24,000 --> 00:11:25,567
My dad. My ex.

160
00:11:25,700 --> 00:11:27,400
They're all the same.

161
00:11:29,767 --> 00:11:31,800
That was harsh.

162
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:33,433
But it's not our fault

163
00:11:33,567 --> 00:11:36,367
if women are the ones
who come after us, right?

164
00:11:36,500 --> 00:11:39,567
You guys only think
about yourselves.

165
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:43,633
You don't even notice how many
people you end up hurting.

166
00:11:43,800 --> 00:11:48,367
Wait. In my defense, I'm not
cheating on anyone, okay?

167
00:11:48,500 --> 00:11:50,633
Any woman
who gets involved with me

168
00:11:50,767 --> 00:11:52,000
knows exactly
what she's getting into.

169
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:54,400
Or what she's not getting into.

170
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:58,333
If they expect more
when they shouldn't,

171
00:11:58,467 --> 00:12:00,133
that's on them.

172
00:12:00,267 --> 00:12:01,100
Okay?

173
00:12:01,233 --> 00:12:04,367
And I don't carry
their emotional baggage,

174
00:12:04,500 --> 00:12:06,300
like what you're doing
right now.

175
00:12:06,433 --> 00:12:07,733
Typical.

176
00:12:07,867 --> 00:12:11,733
All about your own happiness.

177
00:12:11,867 --> 00:12:13,600
Why not, if I can?

178
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:15,533
That's the best thing in life.

179
00:12:19,933 --> 00:12:21,800
Hey, Mister. Let's go straight
to the hotel, okay?

180
00:12:21,933 --> 00:12:24,233
We need to change first.

181
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:41,967
Let's go.

182
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,633
Did you say Mr. Escaño himself
is the one meeting us?

183
00:12:50,767 --> 00:12:52,600
That's what they said.

184
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,033
Is this resort open?

185
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:57,100
Why are there so many people?

186
00:12:57,233 --> 00:12:59,400
Sir, I don't think
they're just guests.

187
00:12:59,533 --> 00:13:01,600
They're brokers and agents, too.

188
00:13:02,667 --> 00:13:04,833
Even better.
More challenging. Let's go.

189
00:13:16,700 --> 00:13:18,233
That's Mr. Escaño.

190
00:13:19,567 --> 00:13:20,733
Come on.

191
00:13:24,633 --> 00:13:26,133
Don't be nervous.

192
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:30,300
Are you nervous? You're still
the prettiest one here.

193
00:13:30,433 --> 00:13:32,533
That's not really the issue.

194
00:13:32,667 --> 00:13:35,367
There are so many of them.

195
00:13:35,500 --> 00:13:38,533
Will he even notice us?

196
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:39,933
That's why you're here.

197
00:13:40,967 --> 00:13:42,233
Okay?

198
00:13:42,367 --> 00:13:44,100
We've got this.

199
00:13:44,233 --> 00:13:45,300
You've got this.

200
00:13:45,433 --> 00:13:47,333
You're Miss Tough Girl,
remember?

201
00:13:48,333 --> 00:13:49,600
Come on.

202
00:14:03,233 --> 00:14:04,567
Mr. Escaño.

203
00:14:05,500 --> 00:14:07,367
- Hi.
- Paolo Torrecampo.

204
00:14:07,500 --> 00:14:09,300
I was expecting you.

205
00:14:10,467 --> 00:14:11,667
Hello, Sir.

206
00:14:11,800 --> 00:14:15,267
Looks like a full house today.

207
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,700
You didn't really think

208
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:21,867
I'd only open
this opportunity to you...

209
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,333
did you?

210
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:32,000
All the major brokerage firms
and independent agents are here.

211
00:14:32,167 --> 00:14:36,067
So Premium Homes Realty
is here, too?

212
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:40,000
That's right. Miss...

213
00:14:40,133 --> 00:14:42,233
- Marjorie Castillo.
- Oh, hi.

214
00:14:42,367 --> 00:14:44,433
She's one of our top associates.

215
00:14:44,567 --> 00:14:46,800
She is also a Cebuano.

216
00:14:48,167 --> 00:14:49,933
You're Bisaya?
No wonder you're beautiful.

217
00:14:50,067 --> 00:14:51,933
Thank you.

218
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:57,133
This is my only granddaughter,
Angeline.

219
00:14:57,267 --> 00:15:03,500
She'll be joining us later for
the Paradiso Escaño site tour.

220
00:15:05,933 --> 00:15:11,833
Many people want the exclusive
listing for this resort.

221
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:13,400
To be honest,

222
00:15:13,533 --> 00:15:19,467
I prefer working with companies
I've worked with before.

223
00:15:19,600 --> 00:15:21,000
So if you really want this deal,

224
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,133
you'll have to impress me
with your pitch.

225
00:15:26,533 --> 00:15:28,233
You won't be disappointed, Sir.

226
00:15:28,367 --> 00:15:30,200
All right. Thank you.

227
00:15:30,333 --> 00:15:31,733
Okay.

228
00:15:33,167 --> 00:15:35,200
- Okay.
- Excuse us.

229
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:44,833
That didn't sound too promising.

230
00:15:45,867 --> 00:15:47,633
But we can still pull this off.

231
00:15:50,467 --> 00:15:51,967
You've been distracted
for a while now.

232
00:15:52,100 --> 00:15:56,400
Do you recognize someone?
Someone you know?

233
00:15:56,533 --> 00:15:59,567
Some people
from my previous company.

234
00:15:59,700 --> 00:16:02,000
At least they're the ones
sent here.

235
00:16:11,433 --> 00:16:13,100
Randall?

236
00:16:45,367 --> 00:16:46,767
That's true.

237
00:16:46,900 --> 00:16:50,100
All right, Brennan. Thanks.
I'll see you later.

238
00:16:50,233 --> 00:16:51,500
Bye.

239
00:17:00,133 --> 00:17:01,867
Love.

240
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:08,433
I got hired at a new firm.

241
00:17:11,733 --> 00:17:15,567
I saw on the tour list that
Torrecampo Realty was included,

242
00:17:15,733 --> 00:17:18,967
so I begged my boss
to send me here.

243
00:17:21,033 --> 00:17:25,267
Love, it's a good thing
your company sent you, right?

244
00:17:25,400 --> 00:17:29,800
I was really praying
you'd be here.

245
00:17:29,933 --> 00:17:31,567
I've wanted to talk to
you for a long time.

246
00:17:31,700 --> 00:17:36,200
Stop calling me "love".
We've been over for a long time.

247
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:37,967
Love, please just hear me out.

248
00:17:38,100 --> 00:17:40,833
Don't touch me!

249
00:17:40,967 --> 00:17:44,000
I'm here to work, Randall.
Leave me alone.

250
00:17:44,133 --> 00:17:46,667
There's nothing
left to talk about.

251
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,533
Just stop.

252
00:17:48,700 --> 00:17:50,967
Marj, please, just talk to me.

253
00:18:38,700 --> 00:18:40,467
Sorry to keep you waiting.

254
00:18:43,700 --> 00:18:46,700
Edward? What are you doing here?

255
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:50,967
Dad said you wanted me
to present to you.

256
00:18:51,100 --> 00:18:54,033
This is just
the initial presentation.

257
00:18:54,167 --> 00:18:57,167
Any agent would've been fine.

258
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,667
But I didn't expect them
to send you personally.

259
00:19:02,067 --> 00:19:03,333
So does that mean it wasn't true

260
00:19:03,467 --> 00:19:05,233
that I was requested
for this account?

261
00:19:12,067 --> 00:19:13,900
Marj, please listen to me.

262
00:19:14,033 --> 00:19:16,700
Let go of me.
Don't you understand Tagalog?

263
00:19:16,833 --> 00:19:18,433
Marj...

264
00:19:18,567 --> 00:19:19,833
She already said she doesn't
want to talk to you.

265
00:19:19,967 --> 00:19:21,633
Don't force it.

266
00:19:21,767 --> 00:19:25,167
And who are you?
Why are you getting involved?

267
00:19:25,300 --> 00:19:28,467
He's my boss. Paolo Torrecampo.

268
00:19:32,833 --> 00:19:34,967
Is this who
you replaced me with?

269
00:19:35,100 --> 00:19:36,833
Is that how you got
into Torrecampo Realty?

270
00:19:36,967 --> 00:19:39,100
Watch what you're saying.

271
00:19:40,100 --> 00:19:42,333
Don't disrespect Marj.

272
00:19:50,200 --> 00:19:52,100
Please, can you not
make a scene here?

273
00:19:52,433 --> 00:19:54,500
All right, Randall.
I'll talk to you.

274
00:19:55,533 --> 00:19:56,400
Are you sure?

275
00:19:56,533 --> 00:19:58,733
Yes, Sir.
It'll just take a moment.

276
00:20:01,067 --> 00:20:02,733
Thank you, Love.

277
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:05,900
Stop calling me that!
It makes me sick.

278
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:22,733
What?

279
00:20:22,867 --> 00:20:25,133
What do you even
want to say to me?

280
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:32,100
I found a buyer for our house.

281
00:20:32,233 --> 00:20:35,100
I'm just fixing
the paperwork now.

282
00:20:35,267 --> 00:20:37,533
I'll finally be able to pay you
what I still owe you.

283
00:20:38,500 --> 00:20:41,500
Good. Just deposit it
into my account.

284
00:20:41,633 --> 00:20:43,833
I need to go.

285
00:20:43,967 --> 00:20:46,167
The familiarization
tour's about to start.

286
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:51,333
- Let go of me.
- Marj, let's get back together.

287
00:20:53,100 --> 00:20:55,133
What?

288
00:20:55,267 --> 00:20:57,067
What are you talking about?

289
00:21:01,133 --> 00:21:02,400
Let's be together again.

290
00:21:02,533 --> 00:21:04,700
Anywhere you want.

291
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:07,267
I'll leave my family
if that's what it takes

292
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:10,733
for you to forgive me
and give me another chance.

293
00:21:10,900 --> 00:21:13,433
Let's continue
what we started.

294
00:21:13,567 --> 00:21:17,100
You can run away with me.
No more problems.

295
00:21:17,233 --> 00:21:19,733
What are you
saying, Randall?

296
00:21:19,867 --> 00:21:21,867
What I mean is...

297
00:21:24,867 --> 00:21:26,633
You're the one I love.

298
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:29,600
Love...

299
00:21:29,733 --> 00:21:32,767
I love you so much. Only you.

300
00:21:37,767 --> 00:21:40,467
Marj, please. Let's be together.

301
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,433
I love you.

302
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:46,267
No!

303
00:21:46,400 --> 00:21:50,300
I don't want to be the reason
your family falls apart.

304
00:21:51,667 --> 00:21:53,867
But Marj, I love you.

305
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:59,100
Your love isn't enough if
it means abandoning your family.

306
00:21:59,233 --> 00:22:01,300
I've been through
that before.

307
00:22:01,433 --> 00:22:02,400
It destroyed me.

308
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:05,833
It hurt my family so badly,
and you know that.

309
00:22:05,967 --> 00:22:08,067
Do you really think
I'd accept you

310
00:22:08,200 --> 00:22:11,167
if you don't understand that?

311
00:22:11,300 --> 00:22:13,767
I do. Believe me.

312
00:22:13,900 --> 00:22:16,567
My only mistake was not
doing the right thing sooner.

313
00:22:20,033 --> 00:22:21,833
I should've stood up for you.

314
00:22:24,233 --> 00:22:26,433
That's what I'm doing now.

315
00:22:26,567 --> 00:22:29,200
I'm choosing you, not treating
you like some mistress.

316
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:32,467
I am choosing you.

317
00:22:35,900 --> 00:22:39,367
Don't you feel any pity
for your wife and child?

318
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:44,200
You really only think
about yourself.

319
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:48,167
I wish I had
seen this sooner.

320
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:53,933
If you truly want
to do the right thing,

321
00:22:54,067 --> 00:22:56,300
leave me alone.

322
00:22:56,433 --> 00:22:58,667
Don't ever bother me again.

323
00:23:05,933 --> 00:23:07,667
I have to admit,

324
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:11,567
Miss Castillo,
your piece was impressive.

325
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:16,200
But I still want
to think it through

326
00:23:16,333 --> 00:23:18,033
before I make a decision.

327
00:23:28,967 --> 00:23:31,100
Sir, is she your wife?

328
00:23:31,233 --> 00:23:32,433
Yeah.

329
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:35,467
This is Donna,
Angeline's grandmother.

330
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:39,833
She's three times your age,
so don't get any ideas.

331
00:23:39,967 --> 00:23:42,467
I wouldn't dare.

332
00:23:42,600 --> 00:23:46,533
How about you?
Aren't you married yet?

333
00:23:46,667 --> 00:23:48,300
Not yet, Sir. Single.

334
00:23:48,433 --> 00:23:50,133
Still having fun.

335
00:23:50,267 --> 00:23:52,267
I was like that, too.

336
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:57,200
I thought being single, ready to
mingle forever, was just fine.

337
00:23:57,367 --> 00:23:59,400
You know how men are.

338
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:02,200
We like to have fun
as long as we can.

339
00:24:03,800 --> 00:24:06,000
But everything changed...

340
00:24:06,133 --> 00:24:08,600
when I met Donna.

341
00:24:08,733 --> 00:24:10,800
She was kind, loving,

342
00:24:10,933 --> 00:24:13,167
and incredibly patient
and understanding.

343
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:18,267
She believed I could change,
that I could be better.

344
00:24:18,400 --> 00:24:20,500
And because of that,

345
00:24:20,633 --> 00:24:24,000
I wanted to become a better man.

346
00:24:24,133 --> 00:24:28,933
You're lucky, Sir.
You found "the one".

347
00:24:29,100 --> 00:24:31,767
Everyone has a perfect match.

348
00:24:31,900 --> 00:24:35,133
Sometimes we're just
surrounded by so many women

349
00:24:35,267 --> 00:24:37,100
we don't really see.

350
00:24:38,067 --> 00:24:40,767
But if you open your eyes,

351
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:43,933
you might realize
the woman meant for you

352
00:24:44,067 --> 00:24:45,800
is already right there.

353
00:24:59,233 --> 00:25:02,500
Good day, Sir Edward.

354
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:04,100
Dad.

355
00:25:04,233 --> 00:25:06,400
Why did you have to lie to me?

356
00:25:06,533 --> 00:25:09,233
Mr. Fuentes never requested me
to present to him.

357
00:25:12,200 --> 00:25:17,967
Didn't you say you wanted
a chance to prove yourself?

358
00:25:18,100 --> 00:25:20,267
Well, there you have it.

359
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,033
You could've just told me.

360
00:25:22,167 --> 00:25:24,867
Instead, you made me
look like a fool.

361
00:25:26,233 --> 00:25:28,833
Watch your tone, Edward.

362
00:25:28,967 --> 00:25:30,700
What are you
really mad about?

363
00:25:30,833 --> 00:25:33,633
That I didn't send you
to Batangas?

364
00:25:33,767 --> 00:25:38,700
The Paradiso Escaño deal needs
the best person for the job.

365
00:25:38,867 --> 00:25:40,500
That is Paolo, not you.

366
00:25:40,633 --> 00:25:42,767
I can close that deal, Dad.

367
00:25:42,900 --> 00:25:44,967
You just need
to give me a chance.

368
00:25:46,667 --> 00:25:48,700
Are you out of your mind?

369
00:25:48,833 --> 00:25:51,467
You think you could
convince Mr. Escaño?

370
00:25:51,600 --> 00:25:53,400
With your personality?

371
00:25:56,633 --> 00:25:58,933
In your dreams, Edward.

372
00:26:03,633 --> 00:26:05,233
In your dreams.

373
00:26:17,967 --> 00:26:19,100
I've decided

374
00:26:19,233 --> 00:26:24,100
who will be Paradiso Escaño's
exclusive realty partner.

375
00:26:24,233 --> 00:26:25,700
- We did it!
- We did it!

376
00:26:27,200 --> 00:26:30,667
I don't believe that you
and my husband are really over.

377
00:26:30,800 --> 00:26:31,800
Leave Marj alone!

378
00:26:31,933 --> 00:26:33,933
She doesn't want you anymore,
don't you get it?

379
00:26:35,433 --> 00:26:37,900
This is exactly
what I was talking about!

380
00:26:38,033 --> 00:26:40,333
Wait, wait! Marj!

381
00:26:40,467 --> 00:26:42,333
You might be overthinking.

382
00:26:42,500 --> 00:26:44,533
Your brother
wouldn't do that.

383
00:26:44,667 --> 00:26:47,733
He knows you're interested
in Marj, right?
